page.title: 16People in Stanwell
page.content:
{Dr Collins } Dr Collins gets up at half past six, the radio wakes him up. He drives for 15min to get to work. First he looks at the mail and then any problems. Surgery starts at nine o'clock. He sees each patient for about five minutes. Then he visits patients too ill to come to the surgery. He usually finishes at half past six. Sometimes he stays in Stanwell overnight incase of emergencies.
{Dr Grigg} Dr Grigg came to school to talk to us because he knows so much about the History of Stanwell. He showed us his collection of pictures. He lives in a house that used to be the old police station. He was very interesting, we learned a lot and he was happy.
